3\u20132014 |year=2013 |publisher=Headline Publishing Group |location=London |isbn=978-0-7553-6413-8 |pages=74\u201375}}</ref>\n*[[Football League Championship]]: [[2014\u201315 Football League Championship|2014\u201315]]<ref>{{cite book |editor-first=John |editor-last=Anderson |title=Sky Sports Football Yearbook 2015\u20132016 |year=2015 |publisher=Headline Publishing Group |location=London |isbn=978-1-4722-2416-3 |pages=68\u201369}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[https://www.qpr.co.uk/squads/first-team/marc-pugh/ Profile] at the Queens Park Rangers F.C. website\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Queens Park Rangers F.C. squad}}\n{{A.F.C. Bournemouth Player of the Year}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pugh, Marc}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Bacup]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Lancashire]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:Burnley F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Kidderminster Harriers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bury F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Shrewsbury Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Luton Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hereford United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:A.F.C. Bournemouth players]]\n[[Category:Hull City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Queens Park Rangers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:English Christians]]\n", "name_user": "Robby.is.on", "label": "safe", "comment": "FixWP:SLASH.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marc_Pugh"}
{"title_page": "List of card games by number of cards", "text_new": "This list arranges [[card games]] by the number of [[playing cards|cards]] used. The description \"classic\" refers to traditional playing cards that are well established today and which are divided into [[card suit]]s. Cards which are not divided into traditional suits, are listed under \"games with proprietary cards\".\n\nWhere two or more packs are listed, games may be predominantly played with just one pack as indicated at the relevant article.\n\n== Games played with classic packs ==\n=== Games played with 16 cards ===\nFrench pack shortened to: (4 suits of 4 cards: Ace, Queen, Jack, Ten)<ref>http://www.pagat.com/de/schafk/kop.html</ref>\n* [[Ba\u015bka]]\n* [[Kop (card game)|Kop]]\n\n=== Games played with 20 cards ===\nGerman pack (4 suits of 5 cards: Deuce, King, Ober, Unter, Ten)<br />\nor French pack shortened to: (4 suits of 5 cards: Ace, King, Queen, Jack, Ten)\n* [[Bauernfangen]]\n* [[Bauernschnapsen]]\n* [[Dreierschnapsen]]\n* [[Schnapsen]]\n\n=== Games played with 24 cards ===\nGerman pack shortened to: (4 suits of 6 cards: Deuce, King, Ober, Unter, Ten, Nine)\n* [[German Solo]] (modern Hombre)\n* [[Mucken|Mucken (shortened pack)]]\n* [[Schafkopf]] ([[Schafkopf#Cards|shortened pack]])\n* [[Sechsundsechzig]] ([[Sixty-Six (card game)|Sixty-Six]])\n\n=== Games played with 32 cards ===\nGerman pack (Schafkopf: 4 suits of 8 cards: Deuce, King, Ober, Unter, Ten, Nine, Eight, Seven)<br />\nor French/Skat/Piquet pack (Skat: 4 suits of 8 cards: Ace, King, Queen, Jack, Ten, Nine, Eight, Seven)\n* [[Bassadewitz]]\n* [[Belote]]\n* [[Bezique]]\n* [[Blattla]]\n* [[Bohemian Schneider]]\n* [[Br\u00e4us|Br\u00e4us/Brus]]\n* [[Brusquembille]]\n* [[Coinche]]\n* [[\u00c9cart\u00e9]]\n* [[Einwerfen]]\n* [[Elfern]]\n* [[Fingerkloppe]]\n* [[F\u00fcnfzehnern]]\n* [[German Schafkopf]]\n* [[German Solo]]\n* [[Grasobern]]\n* [[Klaberjass]]\n* [[Mau Mau (card game)|Mau Mau]]\n* [[Manille]]\n* [[Mariage (card game)|Mariage]]\n* [[Mari\u00e1\u0161]]\n* [[Marjolet]]\n* [[Officers' Skat]]\n* [[Oma Skat]]\n* [[Pr\u00e9f\u00e9rence]]\n* [[Piquet]]\n* [[Quodlibet (card game)|Quodlibet]]\n* [[R\u00e9union (card game)|R\u00e9union]]\n* [[Schafkopf]] ([[Schafkopf#Cards|long pack]])\n* [[Schwimmen]] (Einunddrei\u00dfig, Knack, Schnauz, Wutz, Bull, Hosn obi)\n* [[Sedma]]\n* [[Sheepshead (card game)|Sheepshead]]\n* [[Siebzehn und Vier]]\n* [[Skat (card game)|Skat]]\n* [[Tippen]]\n* [[Ulti]]\n* [[Wallachen]]\n* [[Wendish Schafkopf]]\n\n=== Games played with 33 cards ===\nGerman pack (William Tell/Double German: 4 suits of 8 cards: Deuce, King, Ober, Unter, Ten, Nine, Eight, Seven plus the [[Weli]])\n* [[Bieten]]\n* [[Perlaggen]]\n* [[Watten (card game)|Watten]]\n\n=== Games played with 36 cards ===\nGames played with 36 cards may be of considerable antiquity as the standard German card pack reduced to 32 cards during the 19th century (see Dummett 1980). Several of these games are attempts to play [[Tapp Tarock]] with standard French- or German-suited cards.\n[[French pack]] ([[Jass]]: 4 suits of 9 cards: Ace, King, Queen, Jack, Ten, Nine, Eight, Seven, Six),<br />\n[[German pack]] (Tarock: 4 suits of 9 cards: Deuce, King, Ober, Unter, Ten, Nine, Eight, Seven, Six)<br />\nor [[Swiss pack]] (Jass: 4 suits of 9 cards: Ace, King, Ober, Unter, Banner, Nine, Eight, Seven, Six)\n* [[Bauerntarock]]\n* [[Bavarian Tarock]]\n* [[Dobbm]]\n* [[Durak (card game)|Durak]]\n* [[Hintersche]]\n* [[Jass|Schieber]]\n* [[Tapp (card game)|Tapp]]\n* [[Mau Mau (card game)|Tschau Sepp]]\n\n=== Games played with 40 cards ===\nItalian pack (4 suits of 10 cards: Re, Cavallo, Fante, 7-2, Aceo) or<br />\nSpanish pack (4 suits of 10 cards)\n* [[Bestia (game)|Bestia]]\n* [[Briscola]]\n* [[Landsknecht (card game)|Lansquenet]]\n* [[L\u2019Hombre]]\n* [[Mus (card game)|Mus]]\n* [[Quadrille (card game)|Quadrille]]\n* [[Scopa (card game)|Scopa]]\n* [[Sette e mezzo]]\n* [[Tressette]]\nTarot/Tarock pack shortened to 19 trump cards, Fool and 4 suits of 5 cards:\n* [[Zwanzigerrufen]]\n\n=== Games played with 42 cards ===\nShortened Tarock pack:\n* [[Hungarian Tarock]]\n\n=== Games played with 48 cards ===\nGerman pack or French pack (2 packs each of 4 suits of 6 cards):\n* [[Binokel]]\n* [[Doppelkopf]]\n* [[Gaigel]]\n\n=== Games played with 52 cards ===\nFrench pack (Poker/Bridge) or Anglo-American pack (Poker): (4 suits of 13 cards)\n* [[Badugi]]\n* [[Barbu (card game)|Barbu]]\n* [[Battle (card game)|Battle]] or Battle Royal\n* [[Belle, Fluss and Einunddrei\u00dfig]]\n* [[Bridge (card game)|Bridge]]\n* [[Hearts (card game)|Hearts]]<ref>http://www.pagat.com/de/reverse/hearts.html</ref>\n* [[King (card game)|King]]\n* [[Poker]]\n* [[Whist]]\n\n=== Games played with 54 cards ===\n[[Tarot card games|Tarot/Tarock pack]] shortened to 21 trump cards, Fool and 4 suits of 8 cards:\n* [[Cego]]\n* [[Dreiertarock]]\n* [[Illustrated Tarock]]\n* [[K\u00f6nigrufen]]\n* [[Neunzehnerrufen]]\n* [[Point Tarock]]\n* [[Strohmandeln]]\n* [[Tapp Tarock]]\n\n=== Games played with 58 cards ===\nFrench pack (Zwicker): (4 suits of 13 cards and 6 Jokers) \n* [[Zwicker (card game)|Zwicker]]\n\n=== Games played with 62 cards ===\n78-card Swiss 1JJ Tarot pack minus the 1-4 of Swords and Batons and 7-10 of Cups and Coins:\n* [[Troggu]]\n\n=== Games played with 66 cards ===\n78-card French-suited tarot pack minus the 3 lowest cards of each suit:\n* [[Droggn]]\n\n=== Games played with 78 cards ===\nTarot/Tarock pack (21 trumps, Fool and 4 suits of 14 cards):\n* [[French tarot]]\n* [[Gro\u00dftarock]]\n* [[Scarto]]\n* [[Troccas]]\n\n=== Games played with 97 cards ===\nMinchiate pack (40 trumps, Fool and 4 suits of 14 cards):\n* [[Minchiate]]\n\n=== Games played with 104 cards ===\nFrench pack (Poker/Bridge): 2 packs of 52 cards:\n* [[Zank-Patience|Spite and Malice]]\n\n=== Games played with 108 cards ===\nFrench pack (Canasta): 2 packs of 52 cards and 4 Jokers:\n* [[Canasta]]\n\n=== Games played with 110 cards ===\nFrench pack (Romm\u00e9): 2 packs of 52 cards and 6 Jokers:\n* [[Romm\u00e9]]\n\n=== Games played with 312 cards ===\n(6 packs of 52 cards)\n* [[Baccara (gambling game)|Baccara]]\n* [[Blackjack]]\n\n== Games played with proprietary packs - no additional equipment ==\n=== Games played with 31 cards ===\n* [[Schwarzer Peter (card game)|Schwarzer Peter]] (variant: 2 \u00d7 15 pairs, 1 Schwarzer Peter)\n\n=== Games played with 37 cards ===\n* [[Schwarzer Peter (card game)|Schwarzer Peter]] (variant: 2 \u00d7 18 pairs, 1 Schwarzer Peter)\n\n* [[Tichu]] (4 suits of 13 cards, 4 special cards)\n\n=== Games played with 60 cards ===\n* [[Wizard (card game)|Wizard]] (4 suits of 13 cards, 8 special cards)\n\n=== Games played with 80 cards ===\n* [[The Great Dalmuti]] (78 number cards, 2 Jokers)\n* [[Elfer Raus]] (4 suits of 20 cards)\n\n=== Games played with 81 cards ===\n* [[Set (card game)|Set]]\n\n=== Games played with 108 cards ===\n* [[Uno (card game)|Uno]]\n\n=== Games played with 160 cards ===\n* [[Ligretto]]\n\n=== Games played with 162 cards ===\n* [[Skip-Bo]]\n\n=== Games played with 500 cards ===\n* [[Dominion (card game)|Dominion]]\n\n== Games played with proprietary packs - additional equipment ==\n=== Games played with 16 cards ===\n* [[Love Letter (card game)|Love Letter]]\n\n=== Games played with 55 cards ===\n* [[Jaipur (card game)|Jaipur]]\n\n=== Games played with 60 cards ===\n* [[Hanabi (card game)|Hanabi]]\n\n=== Games played with 63 cards ===\n* [[Caylus Magna Carta]]\n\n=== Games played with 66 cards ===\n* [[23 (card game)|23]]<ref>http://www.amigo-spiele.de/spielregeln</ref> (number cards 1\u201323 in quantity of their value (1x1, 2x2 \u2026 23x23), 12 bonus chips, 50 penalty chips)\n\n=== Games played with 157 cards ===\n* [[7 Wonders (board game)|7 Wonders]]\n\n=== Games played with 160 cards ===\n* [[Race for the Galaxy]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:card games|+]]\n[[Category:Lists of games|Card games sorted by number of cards]]\n", "text_old": "This list arranges [[card games]] by the number of [[playing cards|cards]] used. The description \"classic\" refers to traditional playing cards that are well established today and which are divided into [[card suit]]s. Cards which are not divided into traditional suits, are listed under \"games with proprietary cards\".\n\nWhere two or more packs are listed, games may be predominantly played with just one pack as indicated at the relevant article.\n\n== Games played with classic packs ==\n=== Games played with 16 cards ===\nFrench pack shortened to: (4 suits of 4 cards: Ace, Queen, Jack, Ten)<ref>http://www.pagat.com/de/schafk/kop.html</ref>\n* [[Ba\u015bka]]\n* [[Kop (card game)|Kop]]\n\n=== Games played with 20 cards ===\nGerman pack (4 suits of 5 cards: Deuce, King, Ober, Unter, Ten)<br />\nor French pack shortened to: (4 suits of 5 cards: Ace, King, Queen, Jack, Ten)\n* [[Bauernfangen]]\n* [[Bauernschnapsen]]\n* [[Dreierschnapsen]]\n* [[Schnapsen]]\n\n=== Games played with 24 cards ===\nGerman pack shortened to: (4 suits of 6 cards: Deuce, King, Ober, Unter, Ten, Nine)\n* [[German Solo]] (modern Hombre)\n* [[Mucken|Mucken (shortened pack)]]\n* [[Schafkopf]] ([[Schafkopf#Cards|shortened pack]])\n* [[Sechsundsechzig]] ([[Sixty-Six (card game)|Sixty-Six]])\n\n=== Games played with 32 cards ===\nGerman pack (Schafkopf: 4 suits of 8 cards: Deuce, King, Ober, Unter, Ten, Nine, Eight, Seven)<br />\nor French/Skat/Piquet pack (Skat: 4 suits of 8 cards: Ace, King, Queen, Jack, Ten, Nine, Eight, Seven)\n* [[Bassadewitz]]\n* [[Belote]]\n* [[Bezique]]\n* [[Blattla]]\n* [[Bohemian Schneider]]\n* [[Br\u00e4us|Br\u00e4us/Brus]]\n* [[Brusquembille]]\n* [[Coinche]]\n* [[\u00c9cart\u00e9]]\n* [[Einwerfen]]\n* [[Elfern]]\n* [[Fingerkloppe]]\n* [[F\u00fcnfzehnern]]\n* [[German Schafkopf]]\n* [[German Solo]]\n* [[Grasobern]]\n* [[Klaberjass]]\n* [[Mau Mau (card game)|Mau Mau]]\n* [[Manille]]\n* [[Mariage (card game)|Mariage]]\n* [[Mari\u00e1\u0161]]\n* [[Marjolet]]\n* [[Of